      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DESPICABLE PEDRO (6) turned in a solid run last start over 450m at Maitland finishing 5th and beaten only 4.5 lengths (25.44). Solid record here at the distance winning eight races. Speedy beginner who can find the front despite the tricky draw. Ready to return to form. AUDREY'S MAGIC (1) is a talented type and proved too classy last time to win by one length at this track in a handy 17.56 beating SLICK RAZOR. Safe beginner who draws ideally on the inside. Expecting another bold showing. DESPICABLE LEO (8) was prominent throughout when winning in one of the fastest times of the card two back but could manage only midfield last time when finished 5th and beaten 6 lengths at Maitland (22.75). Good beginner but will need a little luck early crossing from an outside draw. Key runner on best form. ZIPPING MONROE (2) is a last-start placegetter worth considering.",
